<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-06-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-06-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="834" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d834">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.00/678: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chase</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-13"><hi rend="italic">June 13,
                                        1919</hi>.</date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received 10.07
                                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>Have called gunboat <hi rend="italic">Castine</hi>, everybody in
                                danger. Marines needed here at once. City in turmoil. Revolution
                                growing.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chase</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>